More specifically, all the loaf passenger buses delivered to the US
(AFAIK) were "Deluxe Station Wagons" with all that nifty trim.

I once heard a splitty guy get all bent out of shape when he heard someone
refer to my '71 Deluxe SW as a "microbus."  Apparently, the terminology
was important to him!

